    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/372: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-07T16:00:00-03:00"
                            >February 7, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. From Braden. By resolution adopted February 3, special repatriation
                    commission of one officer from each mediatory nation is being set up to
                    supervise repatriation of prisoners under terms of January 21st agreement.
                    Request authorization for designation of Sharp<note n="14" xml:id="d38fn14"
                        >Captain Frederick Dent Sharp, Military Attaché in Argentina.</note> as
                    American member. Duties should be completed within 3 months. [Braden.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
